il_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9769452516434538, \"rank\": 0.023424772865634148, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Schaar was the most complete skateboarder in Wednesday's final, with all three of his runs scoring over 80.\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, his jaw-dropping third run came to an unfortunate end when he failed to stick the landing on a 720 that would have almost certainly put him ahead of Palmer for gold.\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 1058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When Schaar crashed to the ground, all Palmer had to do in his final run was skate to the adoring cheers of the Paris crowd.\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1172, \"end\": 1177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999983394440195, \"rank\": 1.660558749466168e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Palmer is a two-time gold medalist at age 21.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1231, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He and Arisa Trew swept the park competition for Australia, giving the country 15 golds overall.\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1239, \"end\": 1244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\", \"score\": 0.9999999999572537, \"rank\": 4.2753618612479315e-11, \"text\": \"Arisa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\"}, {\"begin\": 1281, \"end\": 1290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.534942304